# Data & Prisma

## Storage roles

| Store | Allowed | Forbidden |
|---|---|---|
| PostgreSQL | Business truth (orders, stock, articles, payments) | — |
| Redis | Cache, queue, lock, rate-limit | Durable order/stock truth |
| S3 | Media bytes | — |
| DB rows | Media metadata / keys | BYTEA / base64 blobs |

## Schema discipline

- Every change → Prisma migration checked in with the feature. No silent prod SQL.
- Public IDs: UUID/ULID strings.
- Status = explicit enums (`OrderStatus`, …), not `isPaid` + `isCancelled` soups.
- Index hot filters: customer orders, variant stock, article/campaign status.
- Soft-delete only when PRD needs recoverability.

## Money (this repo’s convention)

```prisma
totalPaise    Int   @map("total_paise")
amountPaise   Int   @map("amount_paise")
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
const total = priceRupees * 1.18;

// ✅ GOOD — integer paise only; server recomputes from cart lines
subtotalPaise: totals.subtotalPaise,
totalPaise: totals.totalPaise,
```

Never accept client `totalPaise` as authoritative.

## Inventory & transactions

- `onHand` / `reserved` are first-class. Reserve inside the same `$transaction` as order create; release on cancel/failed payment.
- No implicit negative stock.
- Multi-row money/stock writes → `prisma.$transaction`.

## Idempotency

Required for: place-order, payment webhooks (`Payment.idempotencyKey` / event id), campaign award, writer/campaign payout release, bulk stock adjust. Duplicate delivery must not double-charge or double-reserve.
